President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed May 5, 2022, as a National Day of Prayer in the United States. In his proclamation, he acknowledges the significance of prayer throughout American history as a source of strength, comfort, and inspiration. He emphasizes that prayer is a sacred right protected by free speech and religious liberty. President Biden recognizes the healing power of prayer, particularly in the aftermath of the COVID-19 pandemic. He calls for unity and reflection, urging Americans to address challenges such as climate change, attacks on democracy, and the pursuit of liberty, justice, and equality. The proclamation is in accordance with Public Law 100-307, which designates the first Thursday in May as the National Day of Prayer. President Biden invites citizens to give thanks and encourages people of all faiths to join him in seeking God's guidance, mercy, and protection.